A State House press statement issued on Monday, said the deadly accident occurred on Sunday evening when a minibus travelling from Kakonko, Kigoma to Kahama in Shinyanga hit a lorry before colliding with another haulage truck at Nyangozi Village in Biharamulo. The President has been saddened by the incident, the statement said adding that he has asked the Kagera Regional Commissioner to send his condoles to the bereaved families. According to the State House press, Magufuli has reminded road users, especially drivers, to adhere to safety regulations and ordered responsible authorities to double their efforts to save people from such accidents.